<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 3:29PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Sabana Grande, Las
Marias, Lares, San Sebastian, Hormigueros, Moca, northwestern Yauco,
Anasco, Cabo Rojo, Maricao, Mayaguez, Rincon, San German and Aguada
Municipalities through 315 PM AST...
At 227 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was 7 miles southwest of Lares,
extending from southern San Sebastian to Sabana Grande, moving west
at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph, pea sized hail and frequent lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Lightning is one of nature`s
leading killers. If you can hear thunder, you are close
enough to be struck by lightning.
Locations impacted include...
Aguada, Rincon, Las Marias, Mayaguez, Anasco, Sabana Grande,
Hormigueros, Lares, San German, Cabo Rojo, La Playa, Monte Grande,
Luyando, Maricao, Stella, Espino and Sabana Eneas.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency.</instruction>
